    <h4>Wave-Animated Scrollbar</h4>
    <p>Custom scrollbar with the same liquid wave effect as the progress bar. Scroll or drag the thumb to see the wave pattern reveal.</p>

    <div class="button-row" style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
      <button class="aqua-button aqua-button--secondary active" id="arrows-together-btn" onclick="setArrowMode('together')"><span>Arrows Together</span></button>
      <button class="aqua-button aqua-button--secondary" id="arrows-split-btn" onclick="setArrowMode('split')"><span>Arrows Split</span></button>
    </div>

    <%- example(`
      <div class="scrollbar-wave-container" style="width: 300px; height: 220px;" id="scrollbar-wave-demo">
        <div class="scrollbar-wave-content" id="scrollbar-wave-content">
          <div style="padding: 12px;">
            <div style="font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 8px;">Wave Scrollbar Demo</div>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0;">This scrollbar uses the same liquid wave effect as the progress bar, creating a cohesive Aqua experience.</p>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0;">The wave pattern in the thumb creates a sense of depth and movement as you scroll through the content.</p>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0;">Notice how the wave stays fixed relative to the track, revealing different parts of the pattern as the thumb moves.</p>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0;">You can drag the thumb directly or scroll the content area to see the effect.</p>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0;">The design matches the classic Mac OS X Aqua interface with its glossy, three-dimensional appearance.</p>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0;">Try switching between "Arrows Together" and "Arrows Split" modes above!</p>
            <p style="margin: 0;">This implementation responds to theme changes - try switching themes!</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="scrollbar-wave-cap"></div>
        <div class="scrollbar-wave-track" id="scrollbar-wave-track">
          <div class="scrollbar-wave-thumb" id="scrollbar-wave-thumb">
            <div class="scrollbar-wave-ink">
              <div class="scrollbar-wave-shimmer" id="scrollbar-wave-shimmer"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="scrollbar-wave-buttons">
          <button class="scrollbar-wave-btn" id="scrollbar-btn-up" title="Scroll up">▲</button>
          <button class="scrollbar-wave-btn" id="scrollbar-btn-down" title="Scroll down">▼</button>
        </div>
        <!-- Split mode buttons -->
        <button class="scrollbar-wave-btn-top" id="scrollbar-btn-top" title="Scroll up">▲</button>
        <button class="scrollbar-wave-btn-bottom" id="scrollbar-btn-bottom" title="Scroll down">▼</button>
      </div>
    `) %>

